                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.6176 F 51/39: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hood</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-06-20T12:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 20, 1925—noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. The Department has learned that Firestone authorized Ross by cable June 18 to
                    agree to the desires of the Liberian Government regarding all modifications
                    mentioned in your 21, June 14, 2 a.m. Accordingly the Department assumes that
                    the agreements will be signed at once and that the commission will soon proceed
                    to America. Advise probable makeup of commission and date of arrival in order
                    that formal invitation from Firestone may be suitably extended.</p>
                <p>Bussell is preparing to return and will leave when the Department is informed
                    that the agreements have been signed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
